# Naming Conventions

## Variables & Functions
- `camelCase` for variables and functions
- Boolean variables: `isLoading`, `hasError`, `canSubmit`
- Event handlers: `handleClick`, `onSubmit`, `onChange`

## Classes & Components
- `PascalCase` for classes and React components
- File name matches default export name
- Props interface: `{ComponentName}Props`

## Constants
- `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` for global constants
- `camelCase` for module-level constants

## Avoid
- Single-letter variables (except loop counters: i, j, k)
- Hungarian notation (`strName`, `bIsValid`)
- Abbreviations without clear meaning